{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":924,"text":"I live in Washington, D.C.,"},{"time":5112,"text":"but I grew up in Sindhekela, a village in Orissa,\nin India."},{"time":12479,"text":"My father was a government worker."},{"time":16973,"text":"My mother could not read or write, but she"},{"time":20859,"text":"would say to me, \"A king is \nworshipped only in his"},{"time":26303,"text":"own kingdom. A poet is respected everywhere.\""},{"time":32441,"text":"So I wanted to be a poet when I grew up."},{"time":35895,"text":"But I almost didn't go to college"},{"time":40077,"text":"until an aunt offered financial help."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44609,"text":"I went to study in Sambalpur,"},{"time":46794,"text":"the largest town in the region,"},{"time":50989,"text":"where, already in college, I saw a\ntelevision for the first time."},{"time":57988,"text":"I had dreams of going to the United States"},{"time":60148,"text":"for higher studies."},{"time":62748,"text":"When the opportunity came,"},{"time":64877,"text":"I crossed two oceans, with borrowed money"},{"time":67212,"text":"for airfare and only a $20 bill in my pocket."},{"time":73905,"text":"In the U.S., I worked in a research center,"},{"time":78512,"text":"part-time, while taking graduate classes in economics."},{"time":82817,"text":"And with the little I earned, I would"},{"time":88151,"text":"finance myself and then I would send"},{"time":90458,"text":"money home to my brother and my father."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94916,"text":"My story is not unique."},{"time":98285,"text":"There are millions of people who migrate each year."},{"time":102559,"text":"With the help of the family, they cross oceans,"},{"time":106340,"text":"they cross deserts, they cross \nrivers, they cross mountains."},{"time":113155,"text":"They risk their lives to realize a dream,"},{"time":117483,"text":"and that dream is as simple as having a"},{"time":120156,"text":"decent job somewhere so they can send money home"},{"time":123467,"text":"and help the family,"},{"time":125297,"text":"which has helped them before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129954,"text":"There are 232 million international \nmigrants in the world."},{"time":135046,"text":"These are people who live in a country"},{"time":136395,"text":"other than their country of birth."},{"time":139051,"text":"If there was a country made up of"},{"time":140760,"text":"only international migrants,"},{"time":142369,"text":"that would be larger, in population,"},{"time":144426,"text":"than Brazil."},{"time":145863,"text":"That would be larger, in its size"},{"time":147868,"text":"of the economy, than France."},{"time":151070,"text":"Some 180 million of them, from poor countries,"},{"time":155567,"text":"send money home regularly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158718,"text":"Those sums of money are called remittances."},{"time":163743,"text":"Here is a fact that might surprise you:"},{"time":167730,"text":"413 billion dollars, 413 billion dollars"},{"time":172453,"text":"was the amount of remittances sent last year"},{"time":175486,"text":"by migrants to developing countries."},{"time":178522,"text":"Migrants from developing countries,"},{"time":179806,"text":"money sent to developing countries —"},{"time":181950,"text":"413 billion dollars."},{"time":184400,"text":"That's a remarkable number because"},{"time":186120,"text":"that is three times the size of"},{"time":187985,"text":"the total of development aid money."},{"time":191799,"text":"And yet, you and I,"},{"time":195262,"text":"my colleagues in Washington,"},{"time":196768,"text":"we endlessly debate and"},{"time":198765,"text":"discuss about development aid,"},{"time":201193,"text":"while we ignore remittances as small change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205482,"text":"True, people send 200 dollars per month,"},{"time":208635,"text":"on average. But, repeated month after month,"},{"time":212706,"text":"by millions of people,"},{"time":214744,"text":"these sums of money add up to rivers \nof foreign currency."},{"time":218811,"text":"So India, last year, received 72 \nbillion dollars, larger than"},{"time":223905,"text":"its IT exports."},{"time":226361,"text":"In Egypt remittances are three times"},{"time":229345,"text":"the size of revenues from the Suez Canal."},{"time":232917,"text":"In Tajikistan, remittances are 42 percent of GDP."},{"time":236729,"text":"And in poorer countries, smaller \ncountries, fragile countries,"},{"time":239568,"text":"conflict-afflicted countries, remittances are a lifeline,"},{"time":244637,"text":"as in Somalia or in Haiti."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248013,"text":"No wonder these flows have huge"},{"time":250016,"text":"impacts on economies and on poor people."},{"time":254916,"text":"Remittances, unlike private investment money,"},{"time":258725,"text":"they don't flow back at the first"},{"time":261752,"text":"sign of trouble in the country."},{"time":263543,"text":"They actually act like an insurance."},{"time":266428,"text":"When the family is in trouble,"},{"time":268848,"text":"facing hardship, facing hard times,"},{"time":271453,"text":"remittances increase, they act like an insurance."},{"time":273520,"text":"Migrants send more money then."},{"time":276079,"text":"Unlike development aid money,"},{"time":277674,"text":"that must go through official agencies,"},{"time":280251,"text":"through governments, remittances"},{"time":283368,"text":"directly reach the poor,"},{"time":284993,"text":"reach the family,"},{"time":286311,"text":"and often with business advice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288865,"text":"So in Nepal, the share of poor"},{"time":292045,"text":"people was 42 percent in 1995,"},{"time":294873,"text":"the share of poor people in the population."},{"time":297060,"text":"By 2005, a decade later, at a"},{"time":300662,"text":"time of political crisis, economic crisis,"},{"time":303470,"text":"the share of poor people went down to 31 percent."},{"time":307839,"text":"That decline in poverty, most of it,"},{"time":311115,"text":"about half of it, is believed to be"},{"time":313014,"text":"because of remittances from India,"},{"time":315741,"text":"another poor country."},{"time":317880,"text":"In El Salvador, the school dropout"},{"time":322043,"text":"rate among children is lower"},{"time":325281,"text":"in families that receive remittances."},{"time":327087,"text":"In Mexico and Sri Lanka,"},{"time":329056,"text":"the birth weight of children is higher"},{"time":333455,"text":"among families that receive remittances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338869,"text":"Remittances are dollars wrapped with care."},{"time":342568,"text":"Migrants send money home for food,"},{"time":345289,"text":"for buying necessities, for building houses,"},{"time":347541,"text":"for funding education, for funding"},{"time":349929,"text":"healthcare for the elderly, for business"},{"time":352658,"text":"investments for friends and family."},{"time":354916,"text":"Migrants send even more money home"},{"time":357255,"text":"for special occasions like a surgery"},{"time":360003,"text":"or a wedding. And migrants also send"},{"time":363767,"text":"money, perhaps far too many times,"},{"time":366707,"text":"for unexpected funerals that"},{"time":369103,"text":"they cannot attend."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373001,"text":"Much as these flows do all that good,"},{"time":375679,"text":"there are barriers to these"},{"time":377077,"text":"flows of remittances, these"},{"time":378987,"text":"400 billion dollars of remittances."},{"time":381509,"text":"Foremost among them is"},{"time":383490,"text":"the exorbitant cost of sending money home."},{"time":387796,"text":"Money transfer companies structure"},{"time":389793,"text":"their fees to milk the poor."},{"time":393567,"text":"They will say, \"Up to 500 dollars"},{"time":396569,"text":"if you want to send, we will charge you"},{"time":398244,"text":"30 dollars fixed.\""},{"time":400538,"text":"If you are poor and if you have \nonly 200 dollars to send,"},{"time":403634,"text":"you have to pay that $30 fee."},{"time":406876,"text":"The global average cost of sending"},{"time":408911,"text":"money is eight percent."},{"time":411448,"text":"That means you send 100 dollars,"},{"time":412999,"text":"the family on the other side receives only"},{"time":414672,"text":"92 dollars."},{"time":416229,"text":"To send money to Africa,"},{"time":418013,"text":"the cost is even higher:"},{"time":419596,"text":"12 percent."},{"time":420942,"text":"To send money within Africa,"},{"time":422916,"text":"the cost is even higher:"},{"time":424400,"text":"over 20 percent."},{"time":425719,"text":"For example, sending money from Benin \nto Nigeria."},{"time":429588,"text":"And then there is the case of Venezuela, where,"},{"time":433840,"text":"because of exchange controls,"},{"time":435321,"text":"you send 100 dollars and you"},{"time":437321,"text":"are lucky if the family on the other side"},{"time":439339,"text":"receives even 10 dollars."},{"time":442749,"text":"Of course, nobody sends money to Venezuela"},{"time":445693,"text":"through the official channel."},{"time":447316,"text":"It all goes in suitcases."},{"time":449440,"text":"Whereever costs are high,"},{"time":451510,"text":"money goes underground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453893,"text":"And what is worse,"},{"time":455829,"text":"many developing countries actually"},{"time":458160,"text":"have a blanket ban on sending money"},{"time":460407,"text":"out of the country."},{"time":462110,"text":"Many rich nations also have a"},{"time":464247,"text":"blanket ban on sending money \nto specific countries."},{"time":469743,"text":"So, is it that there are no options,"},{"time":471854,"text":"no better options, cheaper options, to send money?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":474487,"text":"There are."},{"time":475278,"text":"M-Pesa in Kenya enables people to send money"},{"time":478998,"text":"and receive money at a fixed cost of only"},{"time":481639,"text":"60 cents per transaction."},{"time":484536,"text":"U.S. Fed started a program with Mexico"},{"time":487402,"text":"to enable money service businesses"},{"time":489041,"text":"to send money to Mexico"},{"time":490619,"text":"for a fixed cost of only 67 cents per transaction."},{"time":495852,"text":"And yet, these faster, cheaper, better options"},{"time":498807,"text":"can't be applied internationally"},{"time":501794,"text":"because of the fear of money laundering,"},{"time":504635,"text":"even though there is little data"},{"time":507486,"text":"to support any connection, any significant"},{"time":510211,"text":"connection between money laundering"},{"time":511883,"text":"and these small remittance transactions."},{"time":517273,"text":"Many international banks now"},{"time":518700,"text":"are wary of hosting bank accounts"},{"time":521589,"text":"of money service businesses, especially"},{"time":524990,"text":"those serving Somalia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527650,"text":"Somalia, a country where the"},{"time":530347,"text":"per capita income is only 250 dollars per year."},{"time":537491,"text":"Monthly remittances, on average, to Somalia"},{"time":539907,"text":"is larger than that amount."},{"time":542219,"text":"Remittances are the lifeblood of Somalia."},{"time":544853,"text":"And yet, this is an example of"},{"time":548574,"text":"the right hand giving a lot of aid,"},{"time":550445,"text":"while the left hand is cutting the lifeblood"},{"time":554463,"text":"to that economy, through regulations."},{"time":560064,"text":"Then there is the case of poor people\nfrom villages, like me."},{"time":564972,"text":"In the villages, the only place where you can"},{"time":566988,"text":"get money is through the post office."},{"time":569720,"text":"Most of the governments in the world"},{"time":571713,"text":"have allowed their post offices to have"},{"time":574729,"text":"exclusive partnerships with money transfer companies."},{"time":577965,"text":"So, if I have to send money to my"},{"time":580787,"text":"father in the village, I must send money"},{"time":583470,"text":"through that particular money transfer company,"},{"time":585773,"text":"even if the cost is high."},{"time":587013,"text":"I cannot go to a cheaper option."},{"time":591325,"text":"This has to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593334,"text":"So, what can international organizations and"},{"time":595585,"text":"social entrepreneurs do to reduce the cost"},{"time":597602,"text":"of sending money home?"},{"time":599231,"text":"First, relax regulations on small remittances\nunder 1,000 dollars."},{"time":605539,"text":"Governments should recognize that"},{"time":607961,"text":"small remittances are not money laundering."},{"time":612208,"text":"Second, governments should abolish exclusive partnerships"},{"time":616647,"text":"between their post office and the money \ntransfer company."},{"time":619641,"text":"For that matter, between the post office"},{"time":621230,"text":"and any national banking system that"},{"time":623257,"text":"has a large network that serves the poor."},{"time":626337,"text":"In fact, they should promote competition,"},{"time":629621,"text":"open up the partnership so that"},{"time":632650,"text":"we will bring down costs like we did,"},{"time":635799,"text":"like they did, in the telecommunications industry."},{"time":639275,"text":"You have seen what has happened there."},{"time":642272,"text":"Third, large nonprofit philanthropic organizations"},{"time":647075,"text":"should create a remittance platform"},{"time":649285,"text":"on a nonprofit basis."},{"time":650868,"text":"They should create a nonprofit"},{"time":651940,"text":"remittance platform to serve the money transfer"},{"time":654140,"text":"companies so that they can send money at a low cost,"},{"time":657869,"text":"while complying with all the complex"},{"time":660020,"text":"regulations all over the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664732,"text":"The development community should"},{"time":666134,"text":"set a goal of reducing remittance costs"},{"time":668411,"text":"to one percent from the current eight percent."},{"time":671664,"text":"If we reduce costs to one percent,"},{"time":673924,"text":"that would release a saving of \n30 billion dollars per year."},{"time":678193,"text":"Thirty billion dollars, that's \nlarger than the entire"},{"time":682594,"text":"bilateral aid budget going to Africa per year."},{"time":685743,"text":"That is larger than, or almost similar to,"},{"time":688759,"text":"the total aid budget of the United States government,"},{"time":691928,"text":"the largest donor on the planet."},{"time":694784,"text":"Actually, the savings would be larger"},{"time":696409,"text":"than that 30 billion because remittance channels"},{"time":698532,"text":"are also used for aid, trade and investment purposes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703939,"text":"Another major impediment to the"},{"time":706410,"text":"flow of remittances reaching the family"},{"time":708664,"text":"is the large and exorbitant"},{"time":711229,"text":"and illegal cost of recruitment,"},{"time":714207,"text":"fees that migrants pay, migrant workers"},{"time":717145,"text":"pay to laborers who found them the job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720409,"text":"I was in Dubai a few years ago."},{"time":724015,"text":"I visited a camp for workers."},{"time":726290,"text":"It was 8 in the evening, dark, hot, humid."},{"time":731603,"text":"Workers were coming back from"},{"time":733415,"text":"their grueling day of work,"},{"time":735886,"text":"and I struck a conversation"},{"time":737670,"text":"with a Bangladeshi construction worker."},{"time":740530,"text":"He was preoccupied that he is sending"},{"time":743439,"text":"money home, he has been"},{"time":744956,"text":"sending money home for a few months now,"},{"time":747866,"text":"and the money is mostly going"},{"time":749369,"text":"to the recruitment agent, to the labor agent"},{"time":752021,"text":"who found him that job."},{"time":753664,"text":"And in my mind, I could picture"},{"time":757408,"text":"the wife waiting for"},{"time":758589,"text":"the monthly remittance."},{"time":760315,"text":"The remittance arrives."},{"time":762080,"text":"She takes the money and hands"},{"time":763809,"text":"it over to the recruitment agent,"},{"time":767379,"text":"while the children are looking on."},{"time":770375,"text":"This has to stop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773705,"text":"It is not only construction \nworkers from Bangladesh,"},{"time":778521,"text":"it is all the workers. There are millions of migrant"},{"time":780227,"text":"workers who suffer from this problem."},{"time":783178,"text":"A construction worker from Bangladesh,"},{"time":784855,"text":"on an average, pays about 4,000 \ndollars in recruitment fees"},{"time":788650,"text":"for a job that gives him only 2,000 \ndollars per year in income."},{"time":794029,"text":"That means that for the two years or three years"},{"time":796759,"text":"of his life, he is basically sending money"},{"time":800252,"text":"to pay for the recruitment fees."},{"time":801536,"text":"The family doesn't get to see any of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805049,"text":"It is not only Dubai, it is the dark"},{"time":808820,"text":"underbelly of every major city in the world."},{"time":811394,"text":"It is not only Bangladeshi construction workers,"},{"time":813892,"text":"it is workers from all over the world."},{"time":816047,"text":"It is not only men."},{"time":817985,"text":"Women are especially vulnerable to"},{"time":819870,"text":"recruitment malpractices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823408,"text":"One of the most exciting and newest"},{"time":828002,"text":"thing happening in the area of remittances"},{"time":830420,"text":"is how to mobilize, through innovation,"},{"time":833461,"text":"diaspora saving and diaspora giving."},{"time":836652,"text":"Migrants send money home,"},{"time":838535,"text":"but they also save a large amount of"},{"time":840168,"text":"money where they live."},{"time":842613,"text":"Annually, migrant savings are estimated"},{"time":845248,"text":"to be 500 billion dollars."},{"time":849349,"text":"Most of that money is parked in"},{"time":851577,"text":"bank deposits that give you zero percent interest rate."},{"time":855302,"text":"If a country were to come \nand offer a three percent"},{"time":858394,"text":"or four percent interest rate, and then say"},{"time":860905,"text":"that the money would be used for building schools,"},{"time":863709,"text":"roads, airports, train systems"},{"time":866844,"text":"in the country of origin, a lot"},{"time":868656,"text":"of migrants would be interested in"},{"time":870593,"text":"parting with their money because"},{"time":872983,"text":"it's not only financial gains that"},{"time":874778,"text":"give them an opportunity"},{"time":876067,"text":"to stay engaged with their country's development."},{"time":881539,"text":"Remittance channels can be used"},{"time":883480,"text":"to sell these bonds to migrants"},{"time":888051,"text":"because when they come"},{"time":889402,"text":"on a monthly basis to send remittances,"},{"time":890985,"text":"that's when you can actually sell\nit to them."},{"time":893566,"text":"You can also do the same"},{"time":894539,"text":"for mobilizing diaspora giving."},{"time":897320,"text":"I would love to invest in a"},{"time":900158,"text":"bullet train system in India"},{"time":902538,"text":"and I would love to contribute to efforts"},{"time":905440,"text":"to fight malaria in my village."},{"time":909356,"text":"Remittances are a great way of"},{"time":913345,"text":"sharing prosperity between places"},{"time":917116,"text":"in a targeted way that benefits"},{"time":919412,"text":"those who need them most."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922348,"text":"Remittances empower people."},{"time":925506,"text":"We must do all we can to make remittances"},{"time":928614,"text":"and recruitment"},{"time":929599,"text":"safer and cheaper."},{"time":931751,"text":"And it can be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":934862,"text":"As for myself, I have been"},{"time":936962,"text":"away from India for two decades now."},{"time":940982,"text":"My wife is a Venezuelan."},{"time":943015,"text":"My children are Americans."},{"time":946913,"text":"Increasingly, I feel like a global citizen."},{"time":950860,"text":"And yet, I am growing nostalgic"},{"time":953190,"text":"about my country of birth."},{"time":956142,"text":"I want to be in India and in the U.S. at the same time."},{"time":961338,"text":"My parents are not there anymore."},{"time":963561,"text":"My brothers and sisters have moved on."},{"time":967063,"text":"There is no real urgency for me to send money home."},{"time":969597,"text":"And yet, from time to time,"},{"time":972219,"text":"I send money home to friends,"},{"time":975070,"text":"to relatives, to the village,"},{"time":977911,"text":"to be there, to stay engaged —"},{"time":980147,"text":"that's part of my identity."},{"time":982195,"text":"And, I'm still striving to be a poet"},{"time":985435,"text":"for the hardworking migrants"},{"time":987803,"text":"and their struggle to break free"},{"time":989340,"text":"of the cycle of poverty."},{"time":990628,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":992402,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}